    • Method Detail

      • setSizeGb

        public SnapshotDiskConfiguration.Builder setSizeGb(Long sizeGb)
        Sets the size of the persistent disk, in GB. If not set the disk will have the size of the snapshot. This value can be larger than the snapshot's size. If the provided size is smaller than the snapshot's size then disk creation will fail.
        Overrides:
        setSizeGb in class DiskConfiguration.Builder<SnapshotDiskConfiguration,SnapshotDiskConfiguration.Builder>
        See Also:
        Restoring a snapshot to a larger size
